-- World Bank Lends $200 Million for Lebanon Water Supply, NNA Says
-- B y   N a y l a   R a z z o u k
-- 2012-02-09T09:23:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-09/world-bank-lends-200-million-for-lebanon-water-supply-nna-says.html
The  World Bank  agreed to lend $200
million loan for a project to divert water to  Beirut  from a
river in southern Lebanon, the National News Agency reported.  The project would supply about 1.7 million residents of the
capital with water from the Awwali River, at a total cost of
$370 million, the state  agency  reported, citing Energy Minister
Gebran Bassil.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nayla Razzouk in Dubai at 
